[5] Indonesia (Jakarta)
Date: Tue 23 Aug 2005
From: A-Lan Banks <A-Lan.Banks@thomson.com>
Source: The Jakarta Post, 23 Aug 2005 [edited]
<http://www.thejakartapost.com/detailcity.asp?fileid=20050823.G06&irec=5>

Almost a month after the start of the dengue epidemic in the capital,
hospitals are still seeing more patients coming in with the disease.
At least 31 new patients were admitted into 3 city hospitals on Monday [22
Aug 2005], with the Budi Asih hospital in East Jakarta recording the
largest number of 20 patients.
Meanwhile, the Tarakan hospital in Central Jakarta and Fatmawati hospital
in South Jakarta received only 2 and 5 new patients, respectively.
There have been no new reports of fatalities. Jakarta health agency
spokeswoman Zelfino said that, from 1 Jan 2005 to Thursday [18 Aug 2005]
last week, there had been a total of 12 036 dengue patients in Jakarta,
with 60 deaths.
