[8] Venezuela
Date: Tue 16 Aug 2005
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: Boletin Epidemiolico Semanal, Semana, 16 Aug 2005 [translated by
Alfonso J. Rodriguez] [edited]
<http://www.msds.gov.ve/msds/Boletines/Alertas/2005/Alerta31.zip>

During the current epidemiological week [3rd week August 2005], 1135 dengue
fever cases were diagnosed; 69 (6.1 percent) of them were dengue
hemorrhagic fever cases. The ratio of dengue fever to dengue hemorrhagic
fever of 15:1.
Cumulative case figures for the year [2005] are 20 323 cases of which 6.3
percent (1278 cases) are of the hemorrhagic form, with the ratio of dengue
fever to dengue hemorrhagic fever of 15:1. The cumulative morbidity rate is
76.5 per 100 000 inhabitants.
Circulating serotypes are 1 and 3. The cumulative case toll for the period
increased by 1.9 percent as compared to the total cumulative number of
cases by the same date [3rd week August] last year [2004].
In the current epidemiological week [3rd week August 2005], no deaths from
dengue have been reported.
A 2.3 percent increase in the number of cases as compared to last week [2nd
week August 2005] was reported, so the situation is considered to be an
epidemic, according to the endemic channel.
52 percent of reported cases are in the less-than-15-years-old age group;
21.5 percent of all cases are in the 15-to-24-years-old age group. Federal
areas that reported the highest case toll are: Carabobo (240), Apure (144),
Mida (135), Barinas (89), and Thira (77).
--
